:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRg_JyPl0X2RleoaLF8OXaAJO0pc2mh2h4NH1OTIEHjv2txBKaI8kJiaX1gYvSjTBEL3bY";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:240;s:6:"height";i:320;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/121315783684290296/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:25:"chair rail molding return";s:4:"slug";s:25:"chair-rail-molding-return";s:5:"title";s:97:"How To Dress Up A Drywall Window Return With Wood Casing Chair Rail Paint Ideas Windows Wood Case";s:3:"alt";s:97:"how to dress up a drywall window return with wood casing chair rail paint ideas windows wood case";s:3:"url";s:99:"https://i.pinimg.com/564x/c1/d0/6c/c1d06c8d5382d48e5310850ef3700cce--house-windows-wood-windows.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTE_UoN6pJGvwasS9UKmNYvDg2-NUuNfIwOOQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:250;s:6:"height";i:510;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/399131585701462178/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:59:{i:0;s:39:"Making a Return for Chair Rail Molding.";i:1;s:45:"Chair rail molding has an elegant look to it.";i:2;s:105:"Its not something you see in every house but when done right can really set apart a room from the others.";i:3;s:115:"If you are installing chair rail in for example a bedroom you can nail it to the walls and stop at the door casing.";i:4;s:82:"The final appearance is that the moldings profile carries all the way to the wall.";i:5;s:79:"Imagine cutting the molding and what you are left with is an ugly straight cut.";i:6;s:40:"With a return you dont see the flat cut.";i:7;s:38:"A return is done by making miter cuts.";i:8;s:98:"On the long piece of molding is a 45-degree miter cut from the wall to the outside of the molding.";i:9;s:72:"This is part of my How to Install Moldings series Historic Example 1928.";i:10;s:166:"When your chair rail pattern projects beyond the door or window trim then the proper way of installing it is to return it on top of the casing and not butted into it.";i:11;s:72:"This example I found in the historic Allen House in Birmingham Michigan.";i:12;s:162:"To create the return you are going to make the opposite 45 degree cut that you made to the chair rail with a 90 degree cut on the other side of that little piece.";i:13;s:103:"The 45 degree cut on the return will abut the chair rail and the 90 degree cut will sit flush with the.";i:14;s:70:"Chair Rail Molding - Best Way For Professional Installation - YouTube.";i:15;s:84:"Chair rail moulding should be placed approximately one-third of the way up the wall.";i:16;s:104:"For example in rooms with 8-foot to 10-foot ceilings the moulding should be placed 28 to 32 inches high.";i:17;s:46:"This keeps the look proportional for the room.";i:18;s:18:"Keep in mind that.";i:19;s:44:"Miter the molding and return it to the wall.";i:20;s:78:"In my opinion this is the best looking option when installing chair rail trim.";i:21;s:81:"Cut the chair rail molding to length mitering the end at 45 outside corner miter.";i:22;s:102:"Miter the end of another piece of molding or scrap then cut off only the mitered point on a miter saw.";i:23;s:154:"The last step for how to cut an end cap for molding is to attach the filler to the original piece of chair rail or whatever type of molding you are using.";i:24;s:53:"To be fast you can use something like DAP Rapid Fuse.";i:25;s:46:"Its like a super glue for woodworking project.";i:26;s:187:"Have you ever stepped inside a home and felt a certain je ne sais quoi an essence or detail you just couldnt put your finger on that nonetheless left you in awe and eager to return again.";i:27;s:169:"Chair rail molding was likely present incorporated in such a subtle and refined manner that one would never suspect its effectuntil implementing it into their own abode.";i:28;s:71:"Chair rail molding also called dado rail is installed about waist high.";i:29;s:73:"Chair rail molding originally was used to protect walls from chair backs.";i:30;s:69:"Today chair rail molding is a common detail in traditional interiors.";i:31;s:130:"Considered decorative by todays standards chair-rail molding adds a feeling of detail and charm to the walls and lends continuity.";i:32;s:30:"Reston Carved Wood Chair-Rail.";i:33;s:15:"3H x 14P x 79L.";i:34;s:51:"You save 20 Reston Carved Wood Chair-Rail quantity.";i:35;s:30:"Reston Carved Wood Chair-Rail.";i:36;s:15:"3H x 14P x 79L.";i:37;s:51:"You save 20 Reston Carved Wood Chair-Rail quantity.";i:38;s:80:"To end chair rail at an archway or corner form a return an inch from the corner.";i:39;s:140:"When you cut the return leave the saw blade down until the blade stops spinning to avoid nicking the return as it falls away from the blade.";i:40;s:53:"First cut a return piece the width of the chair rail.";i:41;s:64:"Chair rail is typically installed 13 up from the floor 32 to 36.";i:42;s:109:"Frieze molding is typically installed just below cornice molding or a few inches below ceiling like a border.";i:43;s:88:"- Start by measuring your room to determine linear footage of chair rail molding needed.";i:44;s:45:"- Add 10 of the total length for miter waste.";i:45;s:77:"The purpose of molding is to establish proper scale and proportion in a room.";i:46;s:187:"And because of its close proximity to us chair rail is often the nearest horizontal molding we see chair rail can do more to make a room feel right than either the baseboard or the crown.";i:47;s:228:"If the chair rail profile protrudes out further than the door or window casing miter the protruding molding back at a 45 angle or form a return by mitering the end of the chair rail and attaching a small sliver of molding to it.";i:48;s:88:"Use finishing nails and construction adhesive to attach chair rail molding to the walls.";i:49;s:91:"Measure the length of the wall and mark a piece of chair rail 18 inch smaller for best fit.";i:50;s:95:"Cut one end of the chair rai